universum.studios.android.fragment

Interface ViewClickWatcher

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ActionBarFragment, BaseFragment, WebFragment

    public interface ViewClickWatcher
    The ViewClickWatcher interface specifies one callback that may be used to dispatch a view click event to a watcher that implements this interface.
    Author:
    Martin Albedinsky

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods

      boolean dispatchViewClick(View view)
      Called to dispatch a view click event to this watcher instance.

        boolean dispatchViewClick(@NonNull
                          View view)
        Called to dispatch a view click event to this watcher instance.
        Parameters:
        view - The clicked view.
        Returns:
        True if this watcher processed the click event for the specified view, false otherwise.
